header.gameNote: AMERICA EAST CONF TR AT VESTAL NY

article.headline: New Hampshire 66, Hartford 62
article.story: VESTAL, N.Y. (AP) -- Mike Christensen scored 22 points, including a pair of free throws to seal the game, to lead New Hampshire to a 66-62 win over Hartford in the America East Conference tournament quarterfinals Saturday night. The Wildcats advance to face Albany in the semifinal round on Sunday. Hartford was down 64-62 with 19.5 seconds to play and had the ball, but Christensen stole a pass for Kenny Adeleke and hit his foul shots on the other end. Adeleke, the conference's leading scorer in the regular season, had 26 points and 13 rebounds. Blagoj Janev added 17 points for fifth-seeded New Hampshire (12-16), which has defeated top seed Albany in both meetings this year. The fourth-seeded Hawks (13-15) got 14 points from Aaron Cook. Hartford took a 36-29 lead into halftime.
